(20, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrian_German', 43796, '', '18', 2013, 'Austria (/ˈɔːstriə/ or /ˈɒstriə/; German: Österreich [ˈøːstɐˌʁaɪç] ), officially the Republic of Austria (German: About this sound Republik Österreich ), is a federal republic and a landlocked country of roughly 8.5 million people in Central Europe. It is bordered by the Czech Republic and Germany to the north, Hungary and Slovakia to the east, Slovenia and Italy to the south, and Switzerland and Liechtenstein to the west.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Austria.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Austria.svg?width=300'),
(21, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azerbaijan', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azerbaijani_language', 10568, '', '76', 2011, 'Azerbaijan (/ˌæzərbaɪˈdʒɑːn/ AZ-ər-by-JAHN; Azerbaijani: Azərbaycan), officially the Republic of Azerbaijan (Azerbaijani: Azərbaycan Respublikası), is the largest country in the Caucasus region located at the crossroads of Western Asia and Eastern Europe. It is bounded by the Caspian Sea to the east, Russia to the north, Georgia to the northwest, Armenia to the west and Iran to the south.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerbaijan', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Azerbaijan.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Azerbaijan.svg?width=300'),
(22, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabic_language', 28691, '34', '48', 2013, 'Bahrain (/bɑːˈreɪn/; Arabic: ‏البحرين‎ About this sound al-Baḥrayn; Persian: ‏بحرین‎ Bahreyn), officially the Kingdom of Bahrain (Arabic: مملكة البحرين‎ About this sound Mamlakat al-Baḥrayn) is a small island country situated near the western shores of the Persian Gulf. It is an archipelago with Bahrain Island, the largest land mass, at 55 km (34 mi) long by 18 km (11 mi) wide.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahrain', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Bahrain.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Bahrain.svg?width=300'),
(23, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangladesh', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bengali_language', 2083, '154', '', 2013, 'Bangladesh /bɑːŋlɑːdɛʃ/; /ˌbæŋɡləˈdæʃ/ (Bengali: বাংলাদেশ, pronounced: [ˈbaŋlad̪eʃ] , lit. "The nation of Bengal"), officially the People''s Republic of Bangladesh (Bengali: গণপ্রজাতন্ত্রী বাংলাদেশ Gônôprôjatôntri Bangladesh), is a country in South Asia. It is bordered by India to its west, north and east; Burma to its southeast and separated from Nepal and Bhutan by the Chicken’s Neck Corridor. To its south, it faces the Bay of Bengal.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Bangladesh.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Bangladesh.svg?width=300'),
