(72, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burundi', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirundi', 625, '', '166', 2013, 'Burundi /bəˈrʊndɨ/, officially the Republic of Burundi (Kirundi: Republika y''Uburundi, [buˈɾundi]; French: République du Burundi, [byˈʁyndi]), is a landlocked country in the African Great Lakes region of Southeast Africa, bordered by Rwanda to the north, Tanzania to the east and south and the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the west. It is also sometimes considered part of Central Africa. Burundi''s capital is Bujumbura.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burundi', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Burundi.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Burundi.svg?width=300'),
(73, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Khmer_language', 2776, '', '138', 2013, 'Cambodia (/kæmˈboʊdiə/; Khmer: កម្ពុជា, Kampuchea, IPA: [kɑmˈpuˈciə]), officially known as the Kingdom of Cambodia (Khmer: ព្រះរាជាណាចក្រកម្ពុជា, Preăh Réachéanachâk Kâmpŭchéa) and once known as the Khmer Empire, is a country located in the southern portion of the Indochina Peninsula in Southeast Asia.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambodia', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Cambodia.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Cambodia.svg?width=300'),
