(126, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_people', 9646, '', '96', 2013, 'The Dominican Republic (/dəˌmɪnɨkən rɨˈpʌblɪk/; Spanish: República Dominicana [reˈpuβlika ðominiˈkana]) is a nation on the island of Hispaniola, part of the Greater Antilles archipelago in the Caribbean region. The western three-eighths of the island is occupied by the nation of Haiti, making Hispaniola one of two Caribbean islands, along with Saint Martin, that are shared by two countries.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominican_Republic', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_Dominican_Republic.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_Dominican_Republic.svg?width=300'),
