(128, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Timor', 'George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, Abraham Lincoln, Alexander Hamilton, Andrew Jackson, Ulysses S. Grant and Benjamin Franklin.', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language', 9467, '', '134', 2013, 'East Timor /ˌiːst ˈtiːmɔr/ or Timor-Leste /tiˈmɔr ˈlɛʃteɪ/, officially the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste, is a country in Southeast Asia. It comprises the eastern half of the island of Timor, the nearby islands of Atauro and Jaco, and Oecusse, an exclave on the northwestern side of the island, within Indonesian West Timor.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Timor', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_East_Timor.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_East_Timor.svg?width=300'),
