(151, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tigrinya_language', 776, '', '181.0', 2011, 'Eritrea (/ˌɛrɨˈtreɪ.ə/ or /ˌɛrɨˈtriːə/; Ge''ez: Tigrinya: ኤርትራ?</span> ʾErtrā ; Arabic: إرتريا‎ Iritriyā), officially the State of Eritrea, is a country in the Horn of Africa. Eritrea is the Italian form of the Greek name Ἐρυθραία (Erythraía ), meaning "red [land]". With its capital at Asmara, it is bordered by Sudan to the west, Ethiopia in the south, and Djibouti in the east.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eritrea', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Eritrea.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Eritrea.svg?width=300'),
