(191, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language', 41248, '15', '5', 2013, 'Germany (/ˈdʒɜrməni/; German: Deutschland), officially the Federal Republic of Germany (German: Bundesrepublik Deutschland, pronounced [ˈbʊndəsʁepuˌbliːk ˈdɔʏtʃlant] ), is a federal parliamentary republic in western-central Europe. The country consists of 16 states and its capital and largest city is Berlin. Germany covers an area of 357,021 square kilometres (137,847 sq mi) and has a largely temperate seasonal climate.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Germany.svg', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Germany.svg?width=300'),
(192, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language', 41248, '15', '5', 2013, 'Germany (/ˈdʒɜrməni/; German: Deutschland), officially the Federal Republic of Germany (German: Bundesrepublik Deutschland, pronounced [ˈbʊndəsʁepuˌbliːk ˈdɔʏtʃlant] ), is a federal parliamentary republic in western-central Europe. The country consists of 16 states and its capital and largest city is Berlin. Germany covers an area of 357,021 square kilometres (137,847 sq mi) and has a largely temperate seasonal climate.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Germany.svg', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Germany.svg?width=300'),
(193, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language', 3718, '', '135', 2013, 'Ghana (/ˈɡɑːnə/), officially called the Republic of Ghana, is a sovereign state and unitary presidential constitutional republic, located along the Gulf of Guinea and Atlantic Ocean, in West Africa. The country is bordered by the Ivory Coast in the west, Burkina Faso in the north, Togo in the east and the Gulf of Guinea and Atlantic Ocean in the south. The word Ghana means "Warrior King".', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghana', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Ghana.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Ghana.svg?width=300'),
(194, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language', 23631, '42', '29', 2013, 'Greece (Greek: Ελλάδα, Elláda, pronounced [eˈlaða] ), officially the Hellenic Republic (Ελληνική Δημοκρατία [eliniˈci ðimokraˈti.a] Ellīnikī́ Dīmokratía) and known since ancient times as Hellas (Greek: Ἑλλάς), is a country in Southern Europe. According to the 2011 census, Greece''s population is around 11 million.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greece', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Greece.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Greece.svg?width=300');
