(198, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language', 5208, '', '131.0', 2011, 'Guatemala, officially the Republic of Guatemala (Spanish: República de Guatemala [reˈpuβlika ðe ɣwateˈmala]), is a country in Central America bordered by Mexico to the north and west, the Pacific Ocean to the southwest, Belize to the northeast, the Caribbean to the east, Honduras to the east and El Salvador to the southeast. It spans an area of 108,890 km2 (42,043 sqmi) and has an estimated population of 15,438,384, making it the most populous state in Central America.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Guatemala.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Guatemala.svg?width=300'),
