(318, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mauritania', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabic_language', 2121, '', '155', 2011, 'Mauritania /mɔrɪˈteɪniə/ (Arabic: موريتانيا‎ Mūrītānyā; Berber: Muritanya or Agawej; Wolof: Gànnaar; Soninke: Murutaane; Pulaar: Moritani), officially the Islamic Republic of Mauritania, is a country in the Maghreb region of western North Africa. It is bordered by the Atlantic Ocean in the west, by Moroccan-controlled Western Sahara in the north, by Algeria in the northeast, by Mali in the east and southeast, and by Senegal in the southwest.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauritania', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mauritania.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mauritania.svg?width=300'),
