(332, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language', 15608, '67', '61.0', 2012, 'Mexico (/ˈmɛksɨkoʊ/; Spanish: México [ˈmexiko] ), officially the United Mexican States (Spanish: About this sound Estados Unidos Mexicanos ), is a federal republic in North America. It is bordered on the north by the United States of America; on the south and west by the Pacific Ocean; on the southeast by Guatemala, Belize, and the Caribbean Sea; and on the east by the Gulf of Mexico.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mexico.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mexico.svg?width=300'),
