(354, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mozambique', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portuguese_language', 1169, '', '184', 2011, 'Mozambique (/moʊzæmbiːk/ or /mɔːzæmbiːk/), officially the Republic of Mozambique (Portuguese: Moçambique or República de Moçambique, pronounced: [ʁɛˈpublikɐ di musɐ̃ˈbiki]), is a country in Southeast Africa bordered by the Indian Ocean to the east, Tanzania to the north, Malawi and Zambia to the northwest, Zimbabwe to the west, and Swaziland and South Africa to the southwest. It is separated from Madagascar by the Mozambique Channel to the east.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mozambique', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mozambique.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Mozambique.svg?width=300'),
