(382, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niger', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language', 771, '', '186', 2012, 'Niger (French pronunciation: ​[niʒɛʁ]; English /niːˈʒɛər/, /ˈnaɪdʒər/), officially the Republic of Niger, is a landlocked country in Western Africa, named after the Niger River. It borders Nigeria and Benin to the south, Burkina Faso and Mali to the west, Algeria and Libya to the north and Chad to the east. Niger covers a land area of almost 1,270,000 km2, making it the largest nation in West Africa, with over 80 percent of its land area covered by the Sahara desert.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Niger.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Niger.svg?width=300'),
