(427, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palau', 'George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, Abraham Lincoln, Alexander Hamilton, Andrew Jackson, Ulysses S. Grant and Benjamin Franklin.', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language', 8100, '119', '49', 2011, 'Palau (/pəˈlaʊ/, sometimes spelled Belau or Pelew), officially the Republic of Palau (Palauan: Beluu er a Belau), is an island country located in the western Pacific Ocean. It is geographically part of the larger island group of Micronesia. The country''s population of around 21,000 is spread across 250 islands forming the western chain of the Caroline Islands. The most populous island is Koror.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palau', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Palau.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Palau.svg?width=300'),
