(431, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panama', 'Balboa Panameña', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language', 16539, '', '59', 2013, 'Panama (/ˈpænəmɑː/ PAN-ə-mah ; Spanish: Panamá ), officially the Republic of Panama (Spanish: República de Panamá [reˈpuβlika ðe panaˈma]), is the southernmost country of Central America and the whole of North America. Situated on the isthmus connecting North and South America, it is bordered by Costa Rica to the west, Colombia to the southeast, the Caribbean to the north and the Pacific Ocean to the south.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Panama.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Panama.svg?width=300'),
