(435, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papua_New_Guinea', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hiri_Motu_language', 2897, '', '153.0', 2011, 'Papua New Guinea (PNG; /ˈpæpə njuː ˈɡɪniː/ PAP-pə-new-GHIN-ee; Tok Pisin: Papua Niugini; Hiri Motu: Papua Niu Gini), officially the Independent State of Papua New Guinea, is an Oceanian country that occupies the eastern half of the island of New Guinea and its offshore islands in Melanesia, a region of the southwestern Pacific Ocean north of Australia. Its capital, located along its southeastern coast, is Port Moresby.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Papua_New_Guinea', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Papua_New_Guinea.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Papua_New_Guinea.svg?width=300'),
