(449, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language', 21118, '49', '39', 2012, 'Poland /ˈpoʊlənd/ (Polish: Polska), officially the Republic of Poland (Polish: Rzeczpospolita Polska), is a country in Central Europe, bordered by Germany to the west; the Czech Republic and Slovakia to the south; Ukraine, Belarus to the east; and the Baltic Sea and Kaliningrad Oblast (a Russian exclave) and Lithuania to the north. The total area of Poland is 312,679 square kilometres (120,726 sq mi), making it the 69th largest country in the world and the 9th largest in Europe.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Poland_(normative).svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Poland_(normative).svg?width=300'),
