(452, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portuguese_language', 23671, '45', '43.0', 2013, 'Portugal (UK /ˈpɔːtʃʊɡl/; US /ˈpɔrtʃʉɡəl/; Portuguese: Portugal [puɾtuˈɣaɫ]), officially the Portuguese Republic (Portuguese: República Portuguesa), is a unitary semi-presidential republic. It is located in South-Western Europe, on the Iberian Peninsula, and it is the westernmost country of mainland Europe, being bordered by the Atlantic Ocean to the west and south and by Spain to the north and east.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portugal', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Portugal.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Portugal.svg?width=300'),
