(477, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kinyarwanda', 1592, '', '167', 2013, 'Rwanda (/ruːˈɑːndə/ or /ruːˈændə/), officially the Republic of Rwanda (Kinyarwanda: Repubulika y''u Rwanda; French: République du Rwanda), is a sovereign state in central and east Africa. Located a few degrees south of the Equator, Rwanda is bordered by Uganda, Tanzania, Burundi and the Democratic Republic of the Congo.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rwanda', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Rwanda.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Rwanda.svg?width=300'),
(478, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/S%C3%A3o_Tom%C3%A9_and_Pr%C3%ADncipe', 'dobra são-tomense', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portuguese_language', 2337, '', '144', 2013, 'São Tomé and Príncipe (/ˌsaʊ təˈmeɪ ən ˈprɪnsɨpə/ SOW-tə-MAY-ən PRIN-si-pə or /ˌsaʊ tɒˈmeɪ ən ˈprɪnsɨpeɪ/ SOW-to-MAY-ən PRIN-si-pay; Portuguese pronunciation: [sɐ̃w̃ tuˈmɛ i ˈpɾĩsɨpɨ] or [sɐ̃w̃ tuˈmɛ i ˈpɾĩsipɨ] if correctly pronounced) officially the Democratic Republic of São Tomé and Príncipe, is a Portuguese-speaking island nation in the Gulf of Guinea, off the western equatorial coast of Central Africa.It consists of two archipelagos around the two main islands: São Tomé and Príncipe, located about 140 kilometres (87 mi) apart and about 250 and 225 kilometres (155 and 140 mi), respectively, off the northwestern coast of Gabon. ', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/São_Tomé_and_Príncipe', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sao_Tome_and_Principe.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sao_Tome_and_Principe.svg?width=300'),
(479, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/S%C3%A3o_Tom%C3%A9_and_Pr%C3%ADncipe', 'dobra são-tomense', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forro_language', 2337, '', '144', 2013, 'São Tomé and Príncipe (/ˌsaʊ təˈmeɪ ən ˈprɪnsɨpə/ SOW-tə-MAY-ən PRIN-si-pə or /ˌsaʊ tɒˈmeɪ ən ˈprɪnsɨpeɪ/ SOW-to-MAY-ən PRIN-si-pay; Portuguese pronunciation: [sɐ̃w̃ tuˈmɛ i ˈpɾĩsɨpɨ] or [sɐ̃w̃ tuˈmɛ i ˈpɾĩsipɨ] if correctly pronounced) officially the Democratic Republic of São Tomé and Príncipe, is a Portuguese-speaking island nation in the Gulf of Guinea, off the western equatorial coast of Central Africa.It consists of two archipelagos around the two main islands: São Tomé and Príncipe, located about 140 kilometres (87 mi) apart and about 250 and 225 kilometres (155 and 140 mi), respectively, off the northwestern coast of Gabon. ', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/São_Tomé_and_Príncipe', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sao_Tome_and_Principe.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sao_Tome_and_Principe.svg?width=300'),
(480, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Kitts_and_Nevis', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language', 15573, '', '62', 2007, 'The Federation of Saint Christopher and Nevis (/seɪnt ˌkɪts ænd ˈniːvɪs/; also known as the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis), located in the Leeward Islands, is a federal two-island country in the West Indies. It is the smallest sovereign state in the Americas, in both area and population.The capital city and headquarters of government for the federated state is Basseterre on the larger island of Saint Kitts.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Kitts_and_Nevis', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Saint_Kitts_and_Nevis.svg', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Saint_Kitts_and_Nevis.svg?width=300'),
