(488, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samoa', 'Samoa tālā', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samoan_language', 5965, '', '96', 2013, 'Samoa (/səˈmoʊ.ə/; Samoan: Sāmoa, IPA: [ˌsaːˈmoa]), officially the Independent State of Samoa (Samoan: Malo Sa''oloto Tuto''atasi o Sāmoa), formerly known as Western Samoa, is a country encompassing the western part of the Samoan Islands in the South Pacific Ocean. It became independent from New Zealand in 1962. The two main islands of Samoa are Upolu and Savai''i, one of the biggest islands in Polynesia.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Samoa.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Samoa.svg?width=300'),
(489, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samoa', 'Samoa tālā', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samoan_language', 5965, '', '96', 2013, 'Samoa (/səˈmoʊ.ə/; Samoan: Sāmoa, IPA: [ˌsaːˈmoa]), officially the Independent State of Samoa (Samoan: Malo Sa''oloto Tuto''atasi o Sāmoa), formerly known as Western Samoa, is a country encompassing the western part of the Samoan Islands in the South Pacific Ocean. It became independent from New Zealand in 1962. The two main islands of Samoa are Upolu and Savai''i, one of the biggest islands in Polynesia.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Samoa.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Samoa.svg?width=300'),
(490, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Marino', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language', 35928, '24', '1.0', 2008, 'San Marino, officially the Republic of San Marino (/sæn məˈriːnoʊ/ san-mə-REE-noh; Italian: Repubblica di San Marino) and also known as the Most Serene Republic of San Marino (Italian: Serenissima Repubblica di San Marino), is an enclaved microstate surrounded by Italy, situated on the Italian Peninsula on the north-eastern side of the Apennine Mountains. Its size is just over 61 km2 (24 sq mi) with an estimated population of over 30,000.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Marino', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_San_Marino.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_San_Marino.svg?width=300'),
(491, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Marino', 'ευρώ (Greek), евро (Bulgarian)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language', 35928, '24', '1.0', 2008, 'San Marino, officially the Republic of San Marino (/sæn məˈriːnoʊ/ san-mə-REE-noh; Italian: Repubblica di San Marino) and also known as the Most Serene Republic of San Marino (Italian: Serenissima Repubblica di San Marino), is an enclaved microstate surrounded by Italy, situated on the Italian Peninsula on the north-eastern side of the Apennine Mountains. Its size is just over 61 km2 (24 sq mi) with an estimated population of over 30,000.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Marino', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_San_Marino.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_San_Marino.svg?width=300'),
(492, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia', 'ريال سعودي', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabic_language', 31309, '28', '57', 2013, 'Saudi Arabia (/ˌsaʊdi əˈreɪbi.ə/ or /ˌsɔːdiː əˈreɪbi.ə/), officially known as the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia (KSA), is the largest Arab state in Western Asia by land area (approximately 2,150,000 km2 (830,000 sq mi), constituting the bulk of the Arabian Peninsula) and the second-largest in the Arab world after Algeria. It is bordered by Jordan and Iraq to the north, Kuwait to the northeast, Qatar, Bahrain and the United Arab Emirates to the east, Oman to the southeast, and Yemen in the south.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Saudi_Arabia.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Saudi_Arabia.svg?width=300'),
