(524, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language', 0, '26', '12', 2013, 'South Korea (About this sound listen), officially the Republic of Korea (Korean: 대한민국; Hanja: 大韓民國; Daehan Minguk About this sound listen; lit. "The Great Republic of Han"), is a country in East Asia, constituting the southern part of the Korean Peninsula. The name Korea is derived from Goryeo, a dynasty which ruled in the Middle Ages. It shares land borders with North Korea to the north, and oversea borders with China to the west and Japan to the east.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_South_Korea.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_South_Korea.svg?width=300'),
