(528, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language', 1978, '', '', 0, 'South Sudan (/ˌsaʊθ suːˈdæn/ or /suːˈdɑːn/), officially the Republic of South Sudan, is a landlocked country in northeastern Africa that gained its independence from Sudan in 2011. Its current capital is Juba, which is also its largest city. The capital city is planned to be changed to the more centrally located Ramciel in the future.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_South_Sudan.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_South_Sudan.svg?width=300'),
