(533, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sri_Lanka', '(இலங்கை ரூபாய்)', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sinhala_language', 6135, '111', '92', 2012, 'Sri Lanka (/sriːˈlɑːŋkə, -ˈlæŋkə/ or /ʃriː-/; Sinhala: ශ්‍රී ලංකාව, śrī laṃkāva, Tamil: இலங்கை, ilaṅkai), officially the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka, is an island country in the northern Indian Ocean off the southern coast of the Indian subcontinent in South Asia; known until 1972 as Ceylon (/sɨˈlɒnˌ seɪ-ˌ siː-/), Sri Lanka has maritime borders with India to the northwest and the Maldives to the southwest.Sri Lanka has a documented history that spans over 3,000 years.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sri_Lanka', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sri_Lanka.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Sri_Lanka.svg?width=300'),
