(578, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language', 31382, '', '49', 2013, 'The Bahamas /bəˈhɑːməz/, officially the Commonwealth of the Bahamas, is an island country consisting of more than 700 islands, cays, and islets in the Atlantic Ocean; north of Cuba and Hispaniola (the Dominican Republic and Haiti); northwest of the Turks and Caicos Islands; southeast of the U.S. state of Florida and east of the Florida Keys. Its capital is Nassau on the island of New Providence.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Bahamas', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_Bahamas.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_Bahamas.svg?width=300'),
(579, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Gambia', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandinka_language', 1864, '', '165', 2013, 'The Gambia (the /ˈɡæmbiə/; officially the Republic of the Gambia) is a country in West Africa. It is surrounded by Senegal, apart from a short strip of Atlantic coastline at its western end. It is the smallest country on mainland Africa.The country is situated on either side of the Gambia River, the nation''s namesake, which flows through the country''s centre and empties into the Atlantic Ocean.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gambia', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_The_Gambia.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_The_Gambia.svg?width=300'),
