(589, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey', 'Türk lirası', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language', 18348, '54', '90', 2013, 'Turkey /ˈtɜrki/ (Turkish: Türkiye), officially the Republic of Turkey (Turkish: About this sound Türkiye Cumhuriyeti ), is a contiguous transcontinental country, located mostly on Anatolia in Western Asia, and on East Thrace in Southeastern Europe. Turkey is bordered by eight countries: Bulgaria to the northwest; Greece to the west; Georgia to the northeast; Armenia, Iran and the Azerbaijani exclave of Nakhchivan to the east; and Iraq and Syria to the southeast.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Turkey.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Turkey.svg?width=300'),
