(601, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuvalu', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuvaluan_language', 3400, '164', '', 0, 'Tuvalu (/tuːˈvɑːluː/ too-VAH-loo or /ˈtuːvəluː/ TOO-və-loo), formerly known as the Ellice Islands, is a Polynesian island nation located in the Pacific Ocean, midway between Hawaii and Australia. It comprises three reef islands and six true atolls spread out between the latitude of 5° to 10° south and longitude of 176° to 180°, west of the International Date Line. Tuvalu''s Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) covers an oceanic area of approximately 900,000 km2.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuvalu', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Tuvalu.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Tuvalu.svg?width=300'),
(602, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine', 'українська гривня', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language', 7422, '', '78', 2012, 'Ukraine (/juːˈkreɪn/; Ukrainian: Україна, transliterated: Ukrayina, [ukrɑˈjinɑ]) is a country in Eastern Europe. It has an area of 603,628 km2 (233,062 sq mi) — including Crimea, which is de facto controlled by neighboring Russia — making it the largest country entirely within Europe.', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Ukraine.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Ukraine.svg?width=300'),
(603, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates', 'درهم إماراتي', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabic_language', 29176, '32', '41.0', 2013, 'The United Arab Emirates /juːˌnaɪtɨd ˌærəb ˈɛmɪrɨts/ (Arabic: دولة الإمارات العربية المتحدة‎ Dawlat al-ʾImārāt al-ʿArabiyyah al-Muttaḥidah), sometimes simply called the Emirates or the UAE, is a country located in the southeast end of the Arabian Peninsula on the Persian Gulf, bordering Oman to the east and Saudi Arabia to the south, as well as sharing sea borders with Qatar, Iran and Pakistan.Established on 2 December 1971, the country is a federation of seven emirates (equivalent to principalities). ', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Arab_Emirates', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg?width=300'),
