(638, 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemen', '', 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabic_language', 2249, '', '160', 2013, 'Yemen /ˈjɛmən/ (Arabic: اليَمَن‎ al-Yaman), officially known as the Republic of Yemen (Arabic: الجمهورية اليمنية‎ al-Jumhūriyyah al-Yamaniyyah), is an Arab country in Western Asia, occupying the southwestern to southern end of the Arabian Peninsula. Yemen is the second largest country in the peninsula, occupying 527,970 km2 (203,850 sq mi). The coastline stretches for about 2,000 km (1,200 mi).', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemen', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Yemen.svg', 'http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Flag_of_Yemen.svg?width=300'),
